<h2>About</h2>

<p>So you found Hacker News and think it's pretty nifty. Only problem is it's very distracting- all that new stuff all the time! You don't want to be tempted to check it every waking moment of the day!</p>

<p>You've tried <a href="http://www.daemonology.net/hn-daily/">HN Daily</a>- it's great that it limits how many stories distract you, but you're still distracted more often than you need.</p>

<p><a href="/">HN Weekly</a> gives you the best of Hacker News once a week, on the day of your choosing. Plow through your side projects and startup stuff six days a week, and save HN for your Friday evening in. Or whenever.</p>

<p>All the fun, now less distracting.</p>

